ArrayList: 
class to implement functionality of resizable-arrays.
Implements list interface of collections framework.

ArrayList vs Array:
Array : Declare the size first and then use it. 
Once size is declared it cannot be changed.
ArrayList: Allows us to create resizable arrays. 
Automatically adjust size when we add or remove elements from them. 
Hence, arraylists are known as dynamic arrays.

How to create an arraylist:
import java.util.ArrayList;
ArrayList<String> al1 = new ArrayList<>();
ArrayList<Integer> al2 = new ArrayList<>();
List<Double> al3 = new ArrayList<>();
List<ClassType> al4 = new ArrayList<>();
